# Local-only sensitive-pattern list for scripts/check-sensitive.sh.
#
# Copy this file to `.git-sensitive-patterns` (which is gitignored) and add the
# REAL strings you never want committed — the patterns live ONLY in that local
# file, so the sensitive values themselves never enter the repository.
#
# One POSIX extended-regex per line. Blank lines and lines starting with '#'
# are ignored. The gate greps each staged file against every pattern.
#
# Examples (edit with your real values, then uncomment in the copied file):
#   your\.name@gmail\.com
#   # home latitude / longitude prefixes (coarse), e.g.:
#   \b51\.4[0-9]{2,}\b
#   \b-0\.1[0-9]{2,}\b
